The physics, ships and graphics are all good, but the opponents ruin it by cheating all the time. Ships with bad handling will pass you in sharp corners, and the ship with the worst acceleration and speed will soar past you on the straights. Even if you are on a boost pad and the opponents aren't, they will still pass you. They won't slow down at all even if they run head on into barriers, when the slightest tap stuns your ship. The opponents can also push you off boost pads with ease. If you ever do good in a race, the opponents will either go impossibly fast, or one will sacrifice them self by running both you an it into the wall, ruining your race. They can destroy you and fling you into the air so easily, and if you ram them, you will only get slowed down. The game is neat, but with the opponents rubber banding and blatantly cheating all the time, it becomes infuriating and impossible to play or win.
